      "item": {
        "id": "045fc059-164f-4c52-ae47-aa70a9d70911",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Some of his conclusions about the psychiatric condition that he designates as \"evil\" are derived from his close study of one patient he names Charlene.<ref name=\"Liemult\" /> Although Charlene is not dangerous, she is ultimately unable to have [[empathy]] for others in any way. According to Peck, people like her see others as play things or tools to be manipulated for their own uses or entertainment. Peck states that these people are rarely seen by psychiatrists, and have never been treated successfully."
