        "text": "* Is consistently self-deceiving, with the intent of avoiding guilt and maintaining a self-image of perfection\n* Deceives others as a consequence of their own self-deception\n* Projects his or her evils and sins onto very specific targets ([[scapegoat]]s) while being apparently normal with everyone else (\"their insensitivity toward him was selective\" (Peck, 1983/1988, p 105<ref name=\"Liemult\" />))\n* Commonly hates with the pretense of love, for the purposes of self-deception as much as deception of others\n* Abuses political (emotional) power (\"the imposition of one's will upon others by overt or covert coercion\" (Peck, 1978/1992, p298<ref name=\"Roadmult\" />))\n* Maintains a high level of respectability, and lies incessantly in order to do so\n* Is consistent in his or her sins. Evil persons are characterized not so much by the magnitude of their sins, but by their consistency (of destructiveness)\n* Is unable to think from the viewpoint of their victim ([[scapegoat]])\n* Has a covert intolerance to criticism and other forms of narcissistic injury"
